#: ../index.en.rst:21
msgid "About QLLVM"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:23
msgid ""
"QLLVM quantum compilation framework is a quantum program compilation "
"framework built on **MLIR** and **LLVM IR**. The framework adopts a "
"three-stage design of front-end, middle-end, and back-end, supporting "
"multiple quantum programming language inputs, and outputting code "
"supported by target hardware after optimization and mapping."
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:26
msgid "Overall Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:28
msgid ""
"QLLVM compiles high-level quantum programs into target back-end "
"executable code, with the following main features:"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:30
msgid ""
"**Multi-language front-end**: Supports OpenQASM 2.0/3.0, Qiskit "
"QuantumCircuit, Q# and other inputs"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:31
msgid ""
"**MLIR optimization**: Single-qubit gate merging, cancellation, diagonal "
"gate removal, gate synthesis and other optimization passes"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:32
msgid ""
"**QIR generation**: Lowering MLIR dialects to QIR (quantum intermediate "
"representation in LLVM IR form)"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:33
msgid ""
"**SABRE mapping**: C++/Qiskit implementation of qubit layout and SWAP "
"insertion"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:34
msgid ""
"**Multi-backend emission**: Output OpenQASM, hardware-specific formats, "
"etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:36
msgid ""
"**Compilation pipeline:** ``` QASM source file → Preprocessing → MLIR "
"(Quantum dialect) → Optimization Passes → Lowering → LLVM IR (QIR) → "
"Backend emission ```"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:42
msgid "Technical Route"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:44
msgid ""
"**Front-end**: Responsible for language parsing and intermediate code "
"generation, converting high-level languages to MLIR Quantum dialect"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:45
msgid ""
"**Middle-end**: Perform quantum program optimization based on MLIR, and "
"further lower MLIR to QIR (LLVM IR)"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:46
msgid ""
"**Back-end**: Based on QIR and QIR runtime library, convert programs to "
"code formats supported by target hardware"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:49
msgid "Key Advantages"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:51
msgid ""
"**Industrial-grade IR infrastructure**: Based on MLIR/LLVM, easy to "
"extend new dialects and new passes"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:52
msgid ""
"**Multiple input forms**: OpenQASM, Qiskit, Q# etc., adapting to "
"different programming habits"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:53
msgid ""
"**Flexible optimization**: -O0/-O1 levels, custom pass sequences, "
"synthesis optimization"
msgstr ""

#: ../index.en.rst:54
msgid ""
"**Physical constraint mapping**: SABRE and other layout and SWAP "
"strategies, adapting to real hardware topology"
msgstr ""

